<div class="rebranding_container">
  <div class="text-image-block_wrapp block-flex-wrap block-gap-50 block-flex-center-sb">
    <div class="text-image-block_wrapp-text block-flex-wrap block-gap-30">
      <h2 class="h2-heading-ss w-100">
        Factory     
        <span class="h2-heading-pp">
          location codes
        </span>
      </h2>
      <p class="body-text">
        Louis Vuitton handbags feature a factory location code, which indicates the country and factory where the handbag was produced. This code consists of two letters, which correspond to a specific factory location. For example, the code “UB” indicates that the handbag was produced in Switzerland, while the code “VX” indicates that it was produced in Germany. 
        <br><br>
        These factory location codes are usually stamped on the interior of the handbag, near the serial number or date code. Understanding these codes is crucial for verifying the authenticity of a Louis Vuitton handbag, as they provide insight into the bag’s origin and manufacturing details.
      </p>
    </div>
    <img class="text-image-block_wrapp-image text-image-block_wrapp-image-small text-image-block_wrapp-image-contain text-image-block_wrapp-image-border" src="{{ "lv_location-codes.webp" | asset_url }}" alt="Authentic Louis Vuitton Factory location codes">
  </div>
</div>

